54 static QCString addTemplateNames(const QCString &s,const QCString &n,const QCString &t)
55 {
56  QCString result;
57  QCString clRealName=n;
58  int p=0,i;
59  if ((i=clRealName.find('<'))!=-1)
60  {
61  clRealName=clRealName.left(i); // strip template specialization
62  }
63  if ((i=clRealName.findRev("::"))!=-1)
64  {
65  clRealName=clRealName.right(clRealName.length()-i-2);
66  }
67  while ((i=s.find(clRealName,p))!=-1)
68  {
69  result+=s.mid(p,i-p);
70  uint j=clRealName.length()+i;
71  if (s.length()==j || (s.at(j)!='<' && !isId(s.at(j))))
72  { // add template names
73  //printf("Adding %s+%s\n",clRealName.data(),t.data());
74  result+=clRealName+t;
75  }
76  else
77  { // template names already present
78  //printf("Adding %s\n",clRealName.data());
79  result+=clRealName;
80  }
81  p=i+clRealName.length();
82  }
83  result+=s.right(s.length()-p);
84  //printf("addTemplateNames(%s,%s,%s)=%s\n",s.data(),n.data(),t.data(),result.data());
85  return result;
86 }

88 // ol.startMemberDocName has already been done before this is called.
89 // when this function returns TRUE, ol.endParameterList will be called.
90 //
91 // typical sequence:
92 // ol.startMemberDoc
93 // ol.startMemberDocName
94 // --- enter writeDefArgumentList
95 // ol.endMemberDocName
96 // ol.startParameterList
97 // ...
98 // ol.startParameterType(first=TRUE)
99 // ol.endParameterType
100 // ol.startParameterName
101 // ol.endParameterName(last==FALSE)
102 // ...
103 // ol.startParameterType(first=FALSE)
104 // ol.endParamtereType
105 // ol.startParameterName
106 // ol.endParameterName(last==TRUE)
107 // ...
108 // --- leave writeDefArgumentList with return value TRUE
109 // ol.endParameterList
110 // ol.endMemberDoc(hasArgs=TRUE)
111 //
112 // For an empty list the function should return FALSE, the sequence is
113 // ol.startMemberDoc
114 // ol.startMemberDocName
115 // --- enter writeDefArgumentList
116 // --- leave writeDefArgumentList with return value FALSE
117 // ol.endMemberDocName
118 // ol.endMemberDoc(hasArgs=FALSE);
119 //
120 
121 static bool writeDefArgumentList(OutputList &ol,Definition *scope,MemberDef *md)
122 {
123  ArgumentList *defArgList=(md->isDocsForDefinition()) ?
124  md->argumentList() : md->declArgumentList();
125  //printf("writeDefArgumentList `%s' isDocsForDefinition()=%d\n",md->name().data(),md->isDocsForDefinition());
126  if (defArgList==0 || md->isProperty())
127  {
128  return FALSE; // member has no function like argument list
129  }
130 
131  // simple argument list for tcl
132  if (md->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Tcl)
133  {
134  if (defArgList->count()==0) return FALSE;
135  ArgumentListIterator ali(*defArgList);
136  Argument *a;
137  ol.endMemberDocName();
138  ol.startParameterList(FALSE);
139  ol.startParameterType(TRUE,0);
140  ol.endParameterType();
141  ol.startParameterName(FALSE);
142  for (;(a=ali.current());++ali)
143  {
144  if (a->defval.isEmpty())
145  {
146  ol.docify(a->name+" ");
147  }
148  else
149  {
150  ol.docify("?"+a->name+"? ");
151  }
152  }
153  ol.endParameterName(TRUE,FALSE,FALSE);
154  return TRUE;
155  }
156 
157  if (!md->isDefine()) ol.docify(" ");
158 
159  //printf("writeDefArgList(%d)\n",defArgList->count());
160  ol.pushGeneratorState();
161  //ol.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Html);
162  bool htmlOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputGenerator::Html);
163  bool latexOn = ol.isEnabled(OutputGenerator::Latex);
164  {
165  // html and latex
166  if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Html);
167  if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
168 
169  ol.endMemberDocName();
170  ol.startParameterList(!md->isObjCMethod());
171  }
172  ol.enableAll();
173  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
174  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
175  {
176  // other formats
177  if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify("("); // start argument list
178  ol.endMemberDocName();
179  }
180  ol.popGeneratorState();
181  //printf("===> name=%s isDefine=%d\n",md->name().data(),md->isDefine());
182 
183  QCString cName;
184  if (scope)
185  {
186  cName=scope->name();
187  int il=cName.find('<');
188  int ir=cName.findRev('>');
189  if (il!=-1 && ir!=-1 && ir>il)
190  {
191  cName=cName.mid(il,ir-il+1);
192  //printf("1. cName=%s\n",cName.data());
193  }
194  else if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && ((ClassDef*)scope)->templateArguments())
195  {
196  cName=tempArgListToString(((ClassDef*)scope)->templateArguments(),scope->getLanguage());
197  //printf("2. cName=%s\n",cName.data());
198  }
199  else // no template specifier
200  {
201  cName.resize(0);
202  }
203  }
204  //printf("~~~ %s cName=%s\n",md->name().data(),cName.data());
205 
206  bool first=TRUE;
207  bool paramTypeStarted=FALSE;
208  bool isDefine = md->isDefine();
209  ArgumentListIterator ali(*defArgList);
210  Argument *a=ali.current();
211  while (a)
212  {
213  if (isDefine || first)
214  {
215  ol.startParameterType(first,0);
216  paramTypeStarted=TRUE;
217  if (isDefine)
218  {
219  ol.endParameterType();
220  ol.startParameterName(TRUE);
221  }
222  }
223  QRegExp re(")("),res("(.*\\*");
224  int vp=a->type.find(re);
225  int wp=a->type.find(res);
226 
227  // use the following to put the function pointer type before the name
228  bool hasFuncPtrType=FALSE;
229 
230  if (!a->attrib.isEmpty() && !md->isObjCMethod()) // argument has an IDL attribute
231  {
232  ol.docify(a->attrib+" ");
233  }
234  if (hasFuncPtrType) // argument type is a function pointer
235  {
236  //printf("a->type=`%s' a->name=`%s'\n",a->type.data(),a->name.data());
237  QCString n=a->type.left(vp);
238  if (hasFuncPtrType) n=a->type.left(wp);
239  if (md->isObjCMethod()) { n.prepend("("); n.append(")"); }
240  if (!cName.isEmpty()) n=addTemplateNames(n,scope->name(),cName);
241  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),md,n);
242  }
243  else // non-function pointer type
244  {
245  QCString n=a->type;
246  if (md->isObjCMethod()) { n.prepend("("); n.append(")"); }
247  if (a->type!="...")
248  {
249  if (!cName.isEmpty()) n=addTemplateNames(n,scope->name(),cName);
250  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),md,n);
251  }
252  }
253  if (!isDefine)
254  {
255  if (paramTypeStarted)
256  {
257  ol.endParameterType();
258  paramTypeStarted=FALSE;
259  }
260  ol.startParameterName(defArgList->count()<2);
261  }
262  if (hasFuncPtrType)
263  {
264  ol.docify(a->type.mid(wp,vp-wp));
265  }
266  if (!a->name.isEmpty() || a->type=="...") // argument has a name
267  {
268  //if (!hasFuncPtrType)
269  //{
270  // ol.docify(" ");
271  //}
272  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
273  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
274  ol.docify(" "); /* man page */
275  if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Html);
276  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
277  ol.startEmphasis();
278  ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Man);
279  if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
280  if (a->name.isEmpty()) ol.docify(a->type); else ol.docify(a->name);
281  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
282  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
283  ol.endEmphasis();
284  ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Man);
285  if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
286  }
287  if (!a->array.isEmpty())
288  {
289  ol.docify(a->array);
290  }
291  if (hasFuncPtrType) // write the part of the argument type
292  // that comes after the name
293  {
294  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),
295  md,a->type.right(a->type.length()-vp));
296  }
297  if (!a->defval.isEmpty()) // write the default value
298  {
299  QCString n=a->defval;
300  if (!cName.isEmpty()) n=addTemplateNames(n,scope->name(),cName);
301  ol.docify(" = ");
302 
303  ol.startTypewriter();
304  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),scope,md->getBodyDef(),md,n,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE);
305  ol.endTypewriter();
306 
307  }
308  ++ali;
309  a=ali.current();
310  if (a)
311  {
312  if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify(", "); // there are more arguments
313  if (!isDefine)
314  {
315  QCString key;
316  if (md->isObjCMethod() && a->attrib.length()>=2)
317  {
318  //printf("Found parameter keyword %s\n",a->attrib.data());
319  // strip [ and ]
320  key=a->attrib.mid(1,a->attrib.length()-2);
321  if (key!=",") key+=":"; // for normal keywords add colon
322  }
323  ol.endParameterName(FALSE,FALSE,!md->isObjCMethod());
324  if (paramTypeStarted)
325  {
326  ol.endParameterType();
327  }
328  ol.startParameterType(FALSE,key);
329  paramTypeStarted=TRUE;
330  }
331  else // isDefine
332  {
333  ol.endParameterName(FALSE,FALSE,TRUE);
334  }
335  }
336  first=FALSE;
337  }
338  ol.pushGeneratorState();
339  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
340  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
341  if (!md->isObjCMethod()) ol.docify(")"); // end argument list
342  ol.enableAll();
343  if (htmlOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Html);
344  if (latexOn) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
345  if (first) ol.startParameterName(defArgList->count()<2);
346  ol.endParameterName(TRUE,defArgList->count()<2,!md->isObjCMethod());
347  ol.popGeneratorState();
348  if (md->extraTypeChars())
349  {
350  ol.docify(md->extraTypeChars());
351  }
352  if (defArgList->constSpecifier)
353  {
354  ol.docify(" const");
355  }
356  if (defArgList->volatileSpecifier)
357  {
358  ol.docify(" volatile");
359  }
360  if (defArgList->refQualifier==RefQualifierLValue)
361  {
362  ol.docify(" &");
363  }
364  else if (defArgList->refQualifier==RefQualifierRValue)
365  {
366  ol.docify(" &&");
367  }
368  if (!defArgList->trailingReturnType.isEmpty())
369  {
370  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol), // out
371  scope, // scope
372  md->getBodyDef(), // fileScope
373  md, // self
374  defArgList->trailingReturnType, // text
375  FALSE // autoBreak
376  );
377 
378  }
379  return TRUE;
380 }

382 static void writeExceptionListImpl(
383  OutputList &ol, ClassDef *cd, MemberDef *md, QCString const& exception)
384 {
385  // this is ordinary exception spec - there must be a '('
386  //printf("exception='%s'\n",exception.data());
387  int index = exception.find('(');
388  if (index!=-1)
389  {
390  ol.exceptionEntry(exception.left(index),false);
391  ++index; // paren in second column so skip it here
392  for (int comma = exception.find(',', index); comma!=-1; )
393  {
394  ++comma; // include comma
395  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,
396  exception.mid(index,comma-index));
397  ol.exceptionEntry(0,false);
398  index=comma;
399  comma = exception.find(',', index);
400  }
401  int close = exception.find(')', index);
402  if (close!=-1)
403  {
404  QCString type=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(exception.mid(index,close-index));
405  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,type);
406  ol.exceptionEntry(0,true);
407  }
408  else
409  {
410  warn(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),
411  "missing ) in exception list on member %s",qPrint(md->name()));
412  }
413  }
414  else // Java Exception
415  {
416  ol.docify(" ");
417  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),cd,md->getBodyDef(),md,exception);
418  }
419 }
420 
421 static void writeExceptionList(OutputList &ol, ClassDef *cd, MemberDef *md)
422 {
423  QCString exception(QCString(md->excpString()).stripWhiteSpace());
424  if ('{'==exception.at(0))
425  {
426  // this is an UNO IDL attribute - need special handling
427  int index = exception.find(';');
428  int oldIndex = 1;
429  while (-1 != index) // there should be no more than 2 (set / get)
430  {
431  // omit '{' and ';' -> "set raises (...)"
432  writeExceptionListImpl(ol,cd,md,exception.mid(oldIndex,index-oldIndex));
433  oldIndex=index+1;
434  index = exception.find(';',oldIndex);
435  }
436  // the rest is now just '}' - omit that
437  }
438  else
439  {
440  writeExceptionListImpl(ol,cd,md,exception);
441  }
442 }

444 static void writeTemplatePrefix(OutputList &ol,ArgumentList *al)
445 {
446  ol.docify("template<");
447  ArgumentListIterator ali(*al);
448  Argument *a = ali.current();
449  while (a)
450  {
451  ol.docify(a->type);
452  ol.docify(" ");
453  ol.docify(a->name);
454  if (a->defval.length()!=0)
455  {
456  ol.docify(" = ");
457  ol.docify(a->defval);
458  }
459  ++ali;
460  a=ali.current();
461  if (a) ol.docify(", ");
462  }
463  ol.docify("> ");
464 }

616 void MemberDefImpl::init(Definition *def,
617  const char *t,const char *a,const char *e,
618  Protection p,Specifier v,bool s,Relationship r,
619  MemberType mt,const ArgumentList *tal,
620  const ArgumentList *al
621  )
622 {
623  classDef=0;
624  fileDef=0;
625  redefines=0;
626  relatedAlso=0;
627  redefinedBy=0;
628  accessorClass=0;
629  nspace=0;
630  memDef=0;
631  memDec=0;
632  group=0;
633  grpId=-1;
634  exampleSDict=0;
635  enumFields=0;
636  enumScope=0;
637  livesInsideEnum=FALSE;
638  defTmpArgLists=0;
639  hasCallGraph = FALSE;
640  hasCallerGraph = FALSE;
641  initLines=0;
642  type=t;
643  if (mt==MemberType_Typedef) type.stripPrefix("typedef ");
644  // type.stripPrefix("struct ");
645  // type.stripPrefix("class " );
646  // type.stripPrefix("union " );
647  type=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(type);
648  args=a;
649  args=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(args);
650  if (type.isEmpty()) decl=def->name()+args; else decl=type+" "+def->name()+args;
651 
652  memberGroup=0;
653  virt=v;
654  prot=p;
655  related=r;
656  stat=s;
657  mtype=mt;
658  exception=e;
659  proto=FALSE;
660  annScope=FALSE;
661  memSpec=0;
662  annMemb=0;
663  annUsed=FALSE;
664  annEnumType=0;
665  groupAlias=0;
666  explExt=FALSE;
667  tspec=FALSE;
668  cachedAnonymousType=0;
669  maxInitLines=Config_getInt(MAX_INITIALIZER_LINES);
670  userInitLines=-1;
671  docEnumValues=FALSE;
672  // copy function template arguments (if any)
673  if (tal)
674  {
675  tArgList = tal->deepCopy();
676  }
677  else
678  {
679  tArgList=0;
680  }
681  //printf("new member al=%p\n",al);
682  // copy function definition arguments (if any)
683  if (al)
684  {
685  defArgList = al->deepCopy();
686  }
687  else
688  {
689  defArgList=0;
690  }
691  // convert function declaration arguments (if any)
692  if (!args.isEmpty())
693  {
694  declArgList = new ArgumentList;
695  stringToArgumentList(args,declArgList,&extraTypeChars);
696  //printf("setDeclArgList %s to %s const=%d\n",args.data(),
697  // argListToString(declArgList).data(),declArgList->constSpecifier);
698  }
699  else
700  {
701  declArgList = 0;
702  }
703  templateMaster = 0;
704  classSectionSDict = 0;
705  docsForDefinition = TRUE;
706  isTypedefValCached = FALSE;
707  cachedTypedefValue = 0;
708  //inbodyLine = -1;

766 MemberDef *MemberDef::deepCopy() const
767 {
768  //MemberDef *result = new MemberDef(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),name());
769  MemberDef *result = new MemberDef(*this);
770  // first copy everything by reference
771  *result->m_impl = *m_impl;
772  // clear pointers owned by object
773  result->m_impl->redefinedBy= 0;
774  result->m_impl->exampleSDict=0;
775  result->m_impl->enumFields=0;
776  result->m_impl->defArgList=0;
777  result->m_impl->tArgList=0;
778  result->m_impl->typeConstraints=0;
779  result->m_impl->defTmpArgLists=0;
780  result->m_impl->classSectionSDict=0;
781  result->m_impl->declArgList=0;
782  // replace pointers owned by the object by deep copies
783  if (m_impl->redefinedBy)
784  {
785  MemberListIterator mli(*m_impl->redefinedBy);
786  MemberDef *md;
787  for (mli.toFirst();(md=mli.current());++mli)
788  {
789  result->insertReimplementedBy(md);
790  }
791  }
792  if (m_impl->exampleSDict)
793  {
794  ExampleSDict::Iterator it(*m_impl->exampleSDict);
795  Example *e;
796  for (it.toFirst();(e=it.current());++it)
797  {
798  result->addExample(e->anchor,e->name,e->file);
799  }
800  }
801  if (m_impl->enumFields)
802  {
803  MemberListIterator mli(*m_impl->enumFields);
804  MemberDef *md;
805  for (mli.toFirst();(md=mli.current());++mli)
806  {
807  result->insertEnumField(md);
808  }
809  }
810  if (m_impl->defArgList)
811  {
812  result->m_impl->defArgList = m_impl->defArgList->deepCopy();
813  }
814  if (m_impl->tArgList)
815  {
816  result->m_impl->tArgList = m_impl->tArgList->deepCopy();
817  }
818  if (m_impl->typeConstraints)
819  {
820  result->m_impl->typeConstraints = m_impl->typeConstraints->deepCopy();
821  }
822  result->setDefinitionTemplateParameterLists(m_impl->defTmpArgLists);
823  if (m_impl->classSectionSDict)
824  {
825  result->m_impl->classSectionSDict = new SDict<MemberList>(7);
826  SDict<MemberList>::IteratorDict it(*m_impl->classSectionSDict);
827  MemberList *ml;
828  for (it.toFirst();(ml=it.current());++it)
829  {
830  result->m_impl->classSectionSDict->append(it.currentKey(),ml);
831  }
832  }
833  if (m_impl->declArgList)
834  {
835  result->m_impl->declArgList = m_impl->declArgList->deepCopy();
836  }
837  return result;
838 }

949 QCString MemberDef::getOutputFileBase() const
950 {
951  static bool separateMemberPages = Config_getBool(SEPARATE_MEMBER_PAGES);
952  static bool inlineSimpleClasses = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
953  QCString baseName;
954 
955  //printf("Member: %s: templateMaster=%p group=%p classDef=%p nspace=%p fileDef=%p\n",
956  // name().data(),m_impl->templateMaster,m_impl->group,m_impl->classDef,
957  // m_impl->nspace,m_impl->fileDef);
958  if (!m_impl->explicitOutputFileBase.isEmpty())
959  {
960  return m_impl->explicitOutputFileBase;
961  }
962  else if (m_impl->templateMaster)
963  {
964  return m_impl->templateMaster->getOutputFileBase();
965  }
966  else if (m_impl->group)
967  {
968  baseName=m_impl->group->getOutputFileBase();
969  }
970  else if (m_impl->classDef)
971  {
972  baseName=m_impl->classDef->getOutputFileBase();
973  if (inlineSimpleClasses && m_impl->classDef->isSimple())
974  {
975  return baseName;
976  }
977  }
978  else if (m_impl->nspace && m_impl->nspace->isLinkableInProject())
979  {
980  baseName=m_impl->nspace->getOutputFileBase();
981  }
982  else if (m_impl->fileDef)
983  {
984  baseName=m_impl->fileDef->getOutputFileBase();
985  }
986 
987  if (baseName.isEmpty())
988  {
989  warn(getDefFileName(),getDefLine(),
990  "Internal inconsistency: member %s does not belong to any"
991  " container!",qPrint(name())
992  );
993  return "dummy";
994  }
995  else if (separateMemberPages && isDetailedSectionLinkable())
996  {
997  if (getEnumScope()) // enum value, which is part of enum's documentation
998  {
999  baseName+="_"+getEnumScope()->anchor();
1000  }
1001  else
1002  {
1003  baseName+="_"+anchor();
1004  }
1005  }
1006  return baseName;
1007 }

1062 void MemberDef::_computeLinkableInProject()
1063 {
1064  static bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
1065  m_isLinkableCached = 2; // linkable
1066  //printf("MemberDef::isLinkableInProject(name=%s)\n",name().data());
1067  if (isHidden())
1068  {
1069  //printf("is hidden\n");
1070  m_isLinkableCached = 1;
1071  return;
1072  }
1073  if (m_impl->templateMaster)
1074  {
1075  //printf("has template master\n");
1076  m_isLinkableCached = m_impl->templateMaster->isLinkableInProject() ? 2 : 1;
1077  return;
1078  }
1079  if (name().isEmpty() || name().at(0)=='@')
1080  {
1081  //printf("name invalid\n");
1082  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // not a valid or a dummy name
1083  return;
1084  }
1085  if (!hasDocumentation() || isReference())
1086  {
1087  //printf("no docs or reference\n");
1088  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // no documentation
1089  return;
1090  }
1091  if (m_impl->group && !m_impl->group->isLinkableInProject())
1092  {
1093  //printf("group but group not linkable!\n");
1094  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // group but group not linkable
1095  return;
1096  }
1097  if (!m_impl->group && m_impl->classDef && !m_impl->classDef->isLinkableInProject())
1098  {
1099  //printf("in a class but class not linkable!\n");
1100  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in class but class not linkable
1101  return;
1102  }
1103  if (!m_impl->group && m_impl->nspace && !m_impl->related && !m_impl->nspace->isLinkableInProject()
1104  && (m_impl->fileDef==0 || !m_impl->fileDef->isLinkableInProject()))
1105  {
1106  //printf("in a namespace but namespace not linkable!\n");
1107  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in namespace but namespace not linkable
1108  return;
1109  }
1110  if (!m_impl->group && !m_impl->nspace &&
1111  !m_impl->related && !m_impl->classDef &&
1112  m_impl->fileDef && !m_impl->fileDef->isLinkableInProject())
1113  {
1114  //printf("in a file but file not linkable!\n");
1115  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // in file (and not in namespace) but file not linkable
1116  return;
1117  }
1118  if (!protectionLevelVisible(m_impl->prot) && m_impl->mtype!=MemberType_Friend)
1119  {
1120  //printf("private and invisible!\n");
1121  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // hidden due to protection
1122  return;
1123  }
1124  if (m_impl->stat && m_impl->classDef==0 && !extractStatic)
1125  {
1126  //printf("static and invisible!\n");
1127  m_isLinkableCached = 1; // hidden due to staticness
1128  return;
1129  }
1130  //printf("linkable!\n");
1131  return; // linkable!
1132 }

1191 void MemberDef::writeLink(OutputList &ol,ClassDef *,NamespaceDef *,
1192  FileDef *fd,GroupDef *gd,bool onlyText)
1193 {
1194  SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
1195  static bool hideScopeNames = Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES);
1196  QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
1197  QCString n = name();
1198  if (!hideScopeNames)
1199  {
1200  if (m_impl->enumScope && m_impl->livesInsideEnum)
1201  {
1202  n.prepend(m_impl->enumScope->displayName()+sep);
1203  }
1204  if (m_impl->classDef && gd && !isRelated())
1205  {
1206  n.prepend(m_impl->classDef->displayName()+sep);
1207  }
1208  else if (m_impl->nspace && (gd || fd))
1209  {
1210  n.prepend(m_impl->nspace->displayName()+sep);
1211  }
1212  }
1213 
1214  if (isObjCMethod())
1215  {
1216  if (isStatic()) ol.docify("+ "); else ol.docify("- ");
1217  }
1218  if (!onlyText && isLinkable()) // write link
1219  {
1220  if (m_impl->mtype==MemberType_EnumValue && getGroupDef()==0 && // enum value is not grouped
1221  getEnumScope() && getEnumScope()->getGroupDef()) // but its container is
1222  {
1223  GroupDef *enumValGroup = getEnumScope()->getGroupDef();
1224  ol.writeObjectLink(enumValGroup->getReference(),
1225  enumValGroup->getOutputFileBase(),
1226  anchor(),n);
1227  }
1228  else
1229  {
1230  ol.writeObjectLink(getReference(),getOutputFileBase(),anchor(),n);
1231  }
1232  }
1233  else // write only text
1234  {
1235  ol.startBold();
1236  ol.docify(n);
1237  ol.endBold();
1238  }
1239 }

1244 ClassDef *MemberDef::getClassDefOfAnonymousType()
1245 {
1246  if (m_impl->cachedAnonymousType) return m_impl->cachedAnonymousType;
1247 
1248  QCString cname;
1249  if (getClassDef()!=0)
1250  {
1251  cname=getClassDef()->name().copy();
1252  }
1253  else if (getNamespaceDef()!=0)
1254  {
1255  cname=getNamespaceDef()->name().copy();
1256  }
1257  QCString ltype(m_impl->type);
1258  // strip `static' keyword from ltype
1259  //if (ltype.left(7)=="static ") ltype=ltype.right(ltype.length()-7);
1260  // strip `friend' keyword from ltype
1261  ltype.stripPrefix("friend ");
1262  static QRegExp r("@[0-9]+");
1263  int l,i=r.match(ltype,0,&l);
1264  //printf("ltype=`%s' i=%d\n",ltype.data(),i);
1265  // search for the last anonymous scope in the member type
1266  ClassDef *annoClassDef=0;
1267  if (i!=-1) // found anonymous scope in type
1268  {
1269  int il=i-1,ir=i+l;
1270  // extract anonymous scope
1271  while (il>=0 && (isId(ltype.at(il)) || ltype.at(il)==':' || ltype.at(il)=='@')) il--;
1272  if (il>0) il++; else if (il<0) il=0;
1273  while (ir<(int)ltype.length() && (isId(ltype.at(ir)) || ltype.at(ir)==':' || ltype.at(ir)=='@')) ir++;
1274 
1275  QCString annName = ltype.mid(il,ir-il);
1276 
1277  // if inside a class or namespace try to prepend the scope name
1278  if (!cname.isEmpty() && annName.left(cname.length()+2)!=cname+"::")
1279  {
1280  QCString ts=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(cname+"::"+annName);
1281  annoClassDef=getClass(ts);
1282  }
1283  // if not found yet, try without scope name
1284  if (annoClassDef==0)
1285  {
1286  QCString ts=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(annName);
1287  annoClassDef=getClass(ts);
1288  }
1289  }
1290  m_impl->cachedAnonymousType = annoClassDef;
1291  return annoClassDef;
1292 }

1297 bool MemberDef::isBriefSectionVisible() const
1298 {
1299  static bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
1300  static bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
1301  static bool briefMemberDesc = Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC);
1302  static bool repeatBrief = Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF);
1303  static bool hideFriendCompounds = Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS);
1304 
1305  //printf("Member %s grpId=%d docs=%s file=%s args=%s\n",
1306  // name().data(),
1307  // 0,"", //grpId,grpId==-1?"<none>":Doxygen::memberDocDict[grpId]->data(),
1308  // "", //getFileDef()->name().data(),
1309  // argsString());
1310 
1311  MemberGroupInfo *info = Doxygen::memGrpInfoDict[m_impl->grpId];
1312  //printf("name=%s m_impl->grpId=%d info=%p\n",name().data(),m_impl->grpId,info);
1313  //QCString *pMemGrp = Doxygen::memberDocDict[grpId];
1314  bool hasDocs = hasDocumentation() ||
1315  // part of a documented member group
1316  (m_impl->grpId!=-1 && info && !(info->doc.isEmpty() && info->header.isEmpty()));
1317 
1318  // only include static members with file/namespace scope if
1319  // explicitly enabled in the config file
1320  bool visibleIfStatic = !(getClassDef()==0 &&
1321  isStatic() &&
1322  !extractStatic
1323  );
1324 
1325  // only include members is the are documented or
1326  // HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS is NO in the config file
1327  bool visibleIfDocumented = (!hideUndocMembers ||
1328  hasDocs ||
1329  isDocumentedFriendClass()
1330  );
1331 
1332  // hide members with no detailed description and brief descriptions
1333  // explicitly disabled.
1334  bool visibleIfEnabled = !(hideUndocMembers &&
1335  documentation().isEmpty() &&
1336  !briefMemberDesc &&
1337  !repeatBrief
1338  );
1339 
1340  // Hide friend (class|struct|union) declarations if HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS is true
1341  bool visibleIfFriendCompound = !(hideFriendCompounds &&
1342  isFriend() &&
1343  (m_impl->type=="friend class" ||
1344  m_impl->type=="friend struct" ||
1345  m_impl->type=="friend union"
1346  )
1347  );
1348 
1349  // only include members that are non-private unless EXTRACT_PRIVATE is
1350  // set to YES or the member is part of a group
1351  bool visibleIfPrivate = (protectionLevelVisible(protection()) ||
1352  m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Friend
1353  );
1354 
1355  // hide member if it overrides a member in a superclass and has no
1356  // documentation of its own
1357  //bool visibleIfDocVirtual = !reimplements() ||
1358  // !Config_getBool(INHERIT_DOCS) ||
1359  // hasDocs;
1360 
1361  // true if this member is a constructor or destructor
1362  bool cOrDTor = isConstructor() || isDestructor();
1363 
1364  // hide default constructors or destructors (no args) without
1365  // documentation
1366  bool visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor = !(cOrDTor &&
1367  m_impl->defArgList &&
1368  (m_impl->defArgList->isEmpty() ||
1369  m_impl->defArgList->getFirst()->type == "void"
1370  ) &&
1371  !hasDocs
1372  );
1373 
1374 
1375  //printf("visibleIfStatic=%d visibleIfDocumented=%d visibleIfEnabled=%d "
1376  // "visibleIfPrivate=%d visibltIfNotDefaultCDTor=%d "
1377  // "visibleIfFriendCompound=%d !annScope=%d\n",
1378  // visibleIfStatic,visibleIfDocumented,
1379  // visibleIfEnabled,visibleIfPrivate,visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor,
1380  // visibleIfFriendCompound,!m_impl->annScope);
1381 
1382  bool visible = visibleIfStatic && visibleIfDocumented &&
1383  visibleIfEnabled && visibleIfPrivate &&
1384  /*visibleIfDocVirtual &&*/ visibleIfNotDefaultCDTor &&
1385  visibleIfFriendCompound &&
1386  !m_impl->annScope && !isHidden();

1869 bool MemberDef::isDetailedSectionLinkable() const
1870 {
1871  static bool extractAll = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_ALL);
1872  static bool alwaysDetailedSec = Config_getBool(ALWAYS_DETAILED_SEC);
1873  static bool repeatBrief = Config_getBool(REPEAT_BRIEF);
1874  static bool briefMemberDesc = Config_getBool(BRIEF_MEMBER_DESC);
1875  static bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
1876  static bool extractStatic = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_STATIC);
1877 
1878  // the member has details documentation for any of the following reasons
1879  bool docFilter =
1880  // treat everything as documented
1881  extractAll ||
1882  // has detailed docs
1883  !documentation().isEmpty() ||
1884  // has inbody docs
1885  !inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty() ||
1886  // is an enum with values that are documented
1887  (m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Enumeration && m_impl->docEnumValues) ||
1888  // is documented enum value
1889  (m_impl->mtype==MemberType_EnumValue && !briefDescription().isEmpty()) ||
1890  // has brief description that is part of the detailed description
1891  (!briefDescription().isEmpty() && // has brief docs
1892  (alwaysDetailedSec && // they are visible in
1893  (repeatBrief || // detailed section or
1894  !briefMemberDesc // they are explicitly not
1895  ) // shown in brief section
1896  )
1897  ) ||
1898  // has a multi-line initialization block
1899  //(initLines>0 && initLines<maxInitLines) ||
1900  (hasMultiLineInitializer() && !hideUndocMembers) ||
1901  // has one or more documented arguments
1902  (m_impl->defArgList!=0 && m_impl->defArgList->hasDocumentation()) ||
1903  // is an attribute or property - need to display that tag
1904  (m_impl->memSpec & (Entry::Attribute|Entry::Property)) ||
1905  // has user comments
1906  Doxygen::userComments
1907  ;
1908 
1909  // this is not a global static or global statics should be extracted
1910  bool staticFilter = getClassDef()!=0 || !isStatic() || extractStatic;
1911 
1912  // only include members that are non-private unless EXTRACT_PRIVATE is
1913  // set to YES or the member is part of a group
1914  bool privateFilter = protectionLevelVisible(protection()) || m_impl->mtype==MemberType_Friend;
1915 
1916  // member is part of an anonymous scope that is the type of
1917  // another member in the list.
1918  //
1919  //bool inAnonymousScope = !briefDescription().isEmpty() && annUsed;
1920 
1921  // hide friend (class|struct|union) member if HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS
1922  // is true
1923  bool friendCompoundFilter = !(Config_getBool(HIDE_FRIEND_COMPOUNDS) &&
1924  isFriend() &&
1925  (m_impl->type=="friend class" ||
1926  m_impl->type=="friend struct" ||
1927  m_impl->type=="friend union"
1928  )
1929  );
1930 
1931 
1932  bool result = ((docFilter && staticFilter && privateFilter && friendCompoundFilter && !isHidden()));
1933  //printf("%s::isDetailedSectionLinkable: %d\n",name().data(),result);
1934  return result;
1935 }

1937 bool MemberDef::isDetailedSectionVisible(bool inGroup,bool inFile) const
1938 {
1939  static bool separateMemPages = Config_getBool(SEPARATE_MEMBER_PAGES);
1940  static bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
1941  static bool hideUndocMembers = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_MEMBERS);
1942  bool groupFilter = getGroupDef()==0 || inGroup || separateMemPages;
1943  bool fileFilter = getNamespaceDef()==0 || !getNamespaceDef()->isLinkable() || !inFile;
1944  bool simpleFilter = (hasBriefDescription() || !hideUndocMembers) && inlineSimpleStructs &&
1945  getClassDef()!=0 && getClassDef()->isSimple();
1946 
1947  bool visible = isDetailedSectionLinkable() && groupFilter && fileFilter &&

1949  bool result = visible || simpleFilter;

1951  // name().data(),result,groupFilter,fileFilter);
1952  return result;

2000  }
2001  if (isAddable()) sl.append("add");

2005  if (isWritable()) sl.append("write");
2006  if (isFinal()) sl.append("final");

2010  if (isSealed()) sl.append("sealed");
2011  if (isNew()) sl.append("new");

2014

2418 QCString MemberDef::displayDefinition() const
2419 {
2420  QCString ldef = definition();
2421  QCString title = name();
2422  if (isEnumerate())
2423  {
2424  if (title.at(0)=='@')
2425  {
2426  ldef = title = "anonymous enum";
2427  if (!m_impl->enumBaseType.isEmpty())
2428  {
2429  ldef+=" : "+m_impl->enumBaseType;
2430  }
2431  }
2432  else
2433  {
2434  ldef.prepend("enum ");
2435  }
2436  }
2437  else if (isEnumValue())
2438  {
2439  if (ldef.at(0)=='@')
2440  {
2441  ldef=ldef.mid(2);
2442  }
2443  }
2444  static QRegExp r("@[0-9]+");
2445  int l,i=r.match(ldef,0,&l);
2446  if (i!=-1) // replace anonymous parts with { ... }
2447  {
2448  int si=ldef.find(' '),pi,ei=i+l;
2449  if (si==-1) si=0;
2450  while ((pi=r.match(ldef,i+l,&l))!=-1)
2451  {
2452  i=pi;
2453  ei=i+l;
2454  }
2455  int ni=ldef.find("::",si);
2456  if (ni>=ei) ei=ni+2;
2457  ldef = ldef.left(si) + " { ... } " + ldef.right(ldef.length()-ei);
2458  }
2459  ClassDef *cd=getClassDef();
2460  if (cd && cd->isObjectiveC())
2461  {
2462  // strip scope name
2463  int ep = ldef.find("::");
2464  if (ep!=-1)
2465  {
2466  int sp=ldef.findRev(' ',ep);
2467  if (sp!=-1)
2468  {
2469  ldef=ldef.left(sp+1)+ldef.mid(ep+2);
2470  }
2471  }
2472  // strip keywords
2473  int dp = ldef.find(':');
2474  if (dp!=-1)
2475  {
2476  ldef=ldef.left(dp+1);
2477  }
2478  l=ldef.length();
2479  //printf("start >%s<\n",ldef.data());
2480  i=l-1;
2481  while (i>=0 && (isId(ldef.at(i)) || ldef.at(i)==':')) i--;
2482  while (i>=0 && isspace((uchar)ldef.at(i))) i--;
2483  if (i>0)
2484  {
2485  // insert braches around the type
2486  QCString tmp("("+ldef.left(i+1)+")"+ldef.mid(i+1));
2487  ldef=tmp;
2488  }
2489  //printf("end >%s< i=%d\n",ldef.data(),i);
2490  if (isStatic()) ldef.prepend("+ "); else ldef.prepend("- ");
2491  }
2492  SrcLangExt lang = getLanguage();
2493  QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang,TRUE);
2494  return substitute(ldef,"::",sep);
2495 }

3019 // strip scope and field name from the type
3020 // example: "struct N::S.v.c" will become "struct v"
3021 static QCString simplifyTypeForTable(const QCString &s)
3022 {
3023  QCString ts=removeAnonymousScopes(s);
3024  if (ts.right(2)=="::") ts = ts.left(ts.length()-2);
3025  static QRegExp re("[A-Z_a-z0-9]+::");
3026  int i,l;
3027  while ((i=re.match(ts,0,&l))!=-1)
3028  {
3029  ts=ts.left(i)+ts.mid(i+l);
3030  }
3031  i=ts.findRev('.');
3032  if (i!=-1) ts = ts.left(i);
3033  i=ts.findRev('.');
3034  if (i!=-1) ts = ts.right(ts.length()-i-1);
3035  //printf("simplifyTypeForTable(%s)->%s\n",s.data(),ts.data());
3036  return ts;
3037 }

3688 void MemberDef::_computeIsConstructor()
3689 {
3690  m_isConstructorCached=1; // FALSE
3691  if (m_impl->classDef)
3692  {
3693  if (m_impl->isDMember) // for D
3694  {
3695  m_isConstructorCached = name()=="this" ? 2 : 1;
3696  return;
3697  }
3698  else if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_PHP) // for PHP
3699  {
3700  m_isConstructorCached = name()=="__construct" ? 2 : 1;
3701  return;
3702  }
3703  else if (name()=="__init__" &&
3704  getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Python) // for Python
3705  {
3706  m_isConstructorCached = 2; // TRUE
3707  return;
3708  }
3709  else if (getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Tcl) // for Tcl
3710  {
3711  m_isConstructorCached = name()=="constructor" ? 2 : 1;
3712  return;
3713  }
3714  else // for other languages
3715  {
3716  QCString locName = m_impl->classDef->localName();
3717  int i=locName.find('<');
3718  if (i==-1) // not a template class
3719  {
3720  m_isConstructorCached = name()==locName ? 2 : 1;
3721  }
3722  else
3723  {
3724  m_isConstructorCached = name()==locName.left(i) ? 2 : 1;
3725  }
3726  return;
3727  }
3728  }
3729 }

3783 void MemberDef::writeEnumDeclaration(OutputList &typeDecl,
3784  ClassDef *cd,NamespaceDef *nd,FileDef *fd,GroupDef *gd)
3785 {
3786  int enumMemCount=0;
3787 
3788  MemberList *fmdl=m_impl->enumFields;
3789  uint numVisibleEnumValues=0;
3790  if (fmdl)
3791  {
3792  MemberListIterator mli(*fmdl);
3793  MemberDef *fmd;
3794  for (mli.toFirst();(fmd=mli.current());++mli)
3795  {
3796  if (fmd->isBriefSectionVisible()) numVisibleEnumValues++;
3797  }
3798  }
3799  if (numVisibleEnumValues==0 && !isBriefSectionVisible())
3800  {
3801  return;
3802  }
3803 
3804  QCString n = name();
3805  int i=n.findRev("::");
3806  if (i!=-1) n=n.right(n.length()-i-2); // strip scope (TODO: is this needed?)
3807  if (n[0]!='@') // not an anonymous enum
3808  {
3809  if (isLinkableInProject() || hasDocumentedEnumValues())
3810  {
3811  //_writeTagData(compoundType);
3812  _addToSearchIndex();
3813  writeLink(typeDecl,cd,nd,fd,gd);
3814  }
3815  else
3816  {
3817  typeDecl.startBold();
3818  typeDecl.docify(n);
3819  typeDecl.endBold();
3820  }
3821  typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
3822  }
3823  if (!m_impl->enumBaseType.isEmpty())
3824  {
3825  typeDecl.writeChar(':');
3826  typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
3827  typeDecl.docify(m_impl->enumBaseType);
3828  typeDecl.writeChar(' ');
3829  }
3830 
3831  uint enumValuesPerLine = (uint)Config_getInt(ENUM_VALUES_PER_LINE);
3832  if (numVisibleEnumValues>0 && enumValuesPerLine>0)
3833  {
3834  typeDecl.docify("{ ");
3835  if (fmdl)
3836  {
3837  MemberListIterator mli(*fmdl);
3838  MemberDef *fmd=mli.current();
3839  bool fmdVisible = fmd ? fmd->isBriefSectionVisible() : TRUE;
3840  while (fmd)
3841  {
3842  if (fmdVisible)
3843  {
3844  /* in html we start a new line after a number of items */
3845  if (numVisibleEnumValues>enumValuesPerLine
3846  && (enumMemCount%enumValuesPerLine)==0
3847  )
3848  {
3849  typeDecl.pushGeneratorState();
3850  typeDecl.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Html);
3851  typeDecl.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
3852  typeDecl.lineBreak();
3853  typeDecl.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
3854  typeDecl.writeString("&#160;&#160;");
3855  typeDecl.popGeneratorState();
3856  }
3857 
3858  if (fmd->hasDocumentation()) // enum value has docs
3859  {
3860  //fmd->_writeTagData(compoundType);
3861  fmd->_addToSearchIndex();
3862  fmd->writeLink(typeDecl,cd,nd,fd,gd);
3863  }
3864  else // no docs for this enum value
3865  {
3866  typeDecl.startBold();
3867  typeDecl.docify(fmd->name());
3868  typeDecl.endBold();
3869  }
3870  if (fmd->hasOneLineInitializer()) // enum value has initializer
3871  {
3872  //typeDecl.writeString(" = ");
3873  typeDecl.writeString(" ");
3874  typeDecl.parseText(fmd->initializer());
3875  }
3876  }
3877 
3878  bool prevVisible = fmdVisible;
3879  ++mli;
3880  fmd=mli.current();
3881  if (fmd && (fmdVisible=fmd->isBriefSectionVisible()))
3882  {
3883  typeDecl.writeString(", ");
3884  }
3885  if (prevVisible)
3886  {
3887  typeDecl.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
3888  typeDecl.writeString("\n"); // to prevent too long lines in LaTeX
3889  typeDecl.enable(OutputGenerator::Man);
3890  enumMemCount++;
3891  }
3892  }
3893  if (numVisibleEnumValues>enumValuesPerLine)
3894  {
3895  typeDecl.pushGeneratorState();
3896  typeDecl.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Html);
3897  typeDecl.lineBreak();
3898  typeDecl.popGeneratorState();
3899  }
3900  }
3901  typeDecl.docify(" }");
3902  }
3903 }

3997 QCString MemberDef::qualifiedName() const
3998 {
3999  if (isObjCMethod())
4000  {
4001  QCString qm;
4002  if (isStatic()) qm="+"; else qm="-";
4003  qm+="[";
4004  qm+=m_impl->classDef->name()+" ";
4005  qm+=name();
4006  qm+="]";
4007  return qm;
4008  }
4009  else if (m_impl->enumScope && m_impl->enumScope->isStrong())
4010  {
4011  return m_impl->enumScope->qualifiedName()+
4012  getLanguageSpecificSeparator(getLanguage())+
4013  localName();
4014  }
4015  else
4016  {
4017  return Definition::qualifiedName();
4018  }
4019 }
